page.title: 17J. W. AUTOMARINE.
page.content: J.W. AUTOMARINE MAKES{LIFTING BAGS}FOR LIFTING THINGS UNDERWATER. THEY ARE MADE WITH VERY STRONG PLASTIC FROM GERMANY, CUT TO SHAPE AND WELDED TOGETHER BY HEAT. 25 PEOPLE WORK THERE, 10 OF THEM IN THE OFFICE. THEY HAVE GOT 12 WELDING MACHINES AND 8 SEWING MACHINES FOR PUTTING THE WEBBING ON. THE WEBBING CAN HOLD UP{5 {TONS}WITHOUT BREAKING. THEY MAKE 1000 BAGS A YEAR, THEY SELL WHAT THEY MAKE. THEY SHIP THINGS TO MANY COUNTRIES THROUGHOUT THE WORLD. PEOPLE ORDER THINGS BY TELEX, TELEPHONE OR BROCHURE. THE FACTORY IS 3 YEARS OLD, THE FIRM IS 12 YEARS OLD. THEY HAVE 2 VANS. A FREIGHT COMPANY MOVES GOODS THEY WORK FROM 8.00 AM TO 4.30 PM. THE OFFICE CLOSES AT 5.00 PM. SOME OF THE BAGS WERE IN A{JAMES BOND FILM. THEY ARE RAPIDLY EXPANDING.
